<DOC><DOCNO> AP881011-0293 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-11-88 2106EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-GoodrichSale     10-11 0132</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Goodrich Sale,0137</SECOND><HEAD>BFGoodrich Negotiating To Sell Aircraft Tire Operations</HEAD><DATELINE>AKRON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Michelin and the BFGoodrich Co. announcedTuesday that they were negotiating the sale of BFGoodrich'saircraft tire operation to Michelin.   BFGoodrich makes brakes and wheels for military and civilaircraft. The company's aircraft tire operations include a Norwood,N.C., factory, retread operations in the United States and Canada,and marketing, sales, research, and testing operations.   David Burner, president of Goodrich's aerospace division, said,``The manufacture of aircraft tires no longer fits our strategy forour growing aerospace division. We are pleased that a company withas strong a commitment and resources as Michelin has will continueto operate this business.''   Final sale of the aircraft tire operation is contingent onapproval from government agencies, the companies said.</TEXT></DOC>